page.title: 20KEWSTOKE AND THE FUTURE
page.content: A survey amongst the Top Junior Class at Kewstoke County Primary School showed only 2 out of 30 children wanted any great change to North Kewstoke.The possibility of a barrier across the Channel was discussed.This seemed to them to have little importance, probably because it had not,as yet, become an important issue.
